\cf2 The systematic uncertainty was recalculated as it was under-estimated due to correlations which increased the error band. Now all physics list agree with data within the uncertainties.\cf3 \
\
- Figure 17.  I don\'92t think I have fully understood the procedure as how you get negative values for the mean time ?  Is there a subtraction that happens ?\
\cf2 The time is defined as t_i - T_ref for the i-th channel. For each bin of radius/energy, a distribution of t_i - T_ref for all channels is done. The mean of this time distribution is then taken in the range [-50, 200] ns. This mean will be dependent of the shape of the distribution especially the tail on the left between -50 and 0 ns. \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
